From 6ece93b644a32a316782b7f6c2a5161c5d154bf9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Oct 2014 17:27:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/9] uas: Add NO_ATA_1X for VIA VL711 devices
Git-Commit: 673029fe9c16c95600bdaca4760673527af32edf
Patch-Mainline: v3.18
References: bnc#914254

Just like some Seagate enclosures, these devices do not seem to grok ata
pass through commands.

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org # 3.16
Signed-off-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Oliver Neukum <oneukum@suse.de>

Conflicts:
	drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h
---
 drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h b/drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h
index b7ed3be..40f68a0 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h
+++ b/drivers/usb/storage/unusual_uas.h
@@ -81,3 +81,18 @@ UNUSUAL_DEV(0x152d, 0x0567, 0x0000, 0x9999,
 		"JMS567",
 		USB_SC_DEVICE, USB_PR_DEVICE, NULL,
 		US_FL_NO_REPORT_OPCODES),
+
+/* Most ASM1051 based devices have issues with uas, blacklist them all */
+/* Reported-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com> */
+UNUSUAL_DEV(0x174c, 0x5106, 0x0000, 0x9999,
+		"ASMedia",
+		"ASM1051",
+		USB_SC_DEVICE, USB_PR_DEVICE, NULL,
+		US_FL_IGNORE_UAS),
+
+/* Reported-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com> */
+UNUSUAL_DEV(0x2109, 0x0711, 0x0000, 0x9999,
+		"VIA",
+		"VL711",
+		USB_SC_DEVICE, USB_PR_DEVICE, NULL,
+		US_FL_NO_ATA_1X),
